               <head>Revenues and description of Bengal</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh94006886 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064915" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4466-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Revenue records, in Persian with raqam annotation, and description of the Province of <name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n81059698" type="place">Bengal</name> until the reign of nominal Timurid or Mughal Emperor ʿĀlamgīr II, and the Navvāb-Nāẓim of Bengal and Orissa, Mīr Jaʿfar ʿAlī Khān Najafī
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated oval seals of James Grant at beginning and end: Jams Grānt ṣadr-i sarishtah'dār (sic) va mulāḥiẓ-i kull-i dafātir az ṭaraf-i dīvān-i ṣūbah'jāt-i Bangālah va Bihār va gairah, madār al-mahām sipah sālār-i Angrīz-i Kampanī, sanah 1193 Bangalah </p>
                        <p>First section (ff. 1-103) bears the dated square and circular seals, respectively, of: 1) Muḥammad Ḥusayn bandah-'i dargāh [regnal year] 5; 2) Dāʾim Allāh bandah-'i ʿĀlamgīr [II] Pādshāh-i Ghāzī [regnal year] aḥad (=1) </p>
                        <p>Not dated and lacking colophon </p>
                        <p>Not foliated; 132 ff. approximately (103 + 26 + 3 ff)</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                  </msItem>
